  "doc_id": "31711",
  "text": "In a study of 26 azacitidine-treated patients, a 38% response rate (median time to response: 9 months) with an OS of 8 months was reported. Interestingly, the authors observed better responses in post-ET, as opposed to post-PV, MPN-BP, though with no significant OS difference [CITATION_1] . Another study which reviewed MPN-BP patients treated with azacitidine found a median OS better than that of their historical controls (9.9 months). Once again, the median survival of patients achieving a complete response (CR) was even better at 19.6 months [CITATION_2] .",
